complete. Besides, mechanisms and interventions cannot actually be combined in the way usually done in the literature. This book offers solutions to both these problems based on insights from experimental practice. It defends a new reading of the interventionist account, highlights the importance of non-interventionist studies for scientific inquiry, and supplies a taxonomy of experiments that makes it easy to see how the gaps in contemporary accounts of scientific explanation can be filled. The book concludes that a truly empirically adequate philosophy of science must take into account a much wider range of experimental research than has been done to date. With the taxonomy provided, this book serves a stepping-stone leading into a new era of philosophy of science-for cognitive neuroscience and beyond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2019) 0aCognitive neurosciencexPhilosophy. 0aElectronic books. 4aInterventionismus. 4aNeuroscience. 4aNeurowissenschaften. 4aWissenschaftstheorie. 4ainterventionist causation. 4aphilosophy of science. 70(DE-601)1052245960(DE-588)4193780-6aKognitionswissenschaft2gnd 70(DE-601)1056628520(DE-588)4135740-1aNeuropsychologie2gnd 70(DE-601)1062002590(DE-588)4045791-6aPhilosophie2gnd 7aPHILOSOPHY / Epistemology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2017z9783110548228oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831105292030 cprintz978311052737740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110530940423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110530940.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_P